net.egartley.beyondorigins.objects

Class Animation

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.egartley.beyondorigins.objects.Animation

  • public class Animation
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a collection of AnimationFrame objects, which can be used for animating a Sprite
    Author:
    Evan Gartley
    See Also:
    AnimationFrame, Sprite, AnimatedEntity

      • setThreshold

        public void setThreshold(int t)

        Sets the animation's threshold, or interval, for when to go to the next frame

        The tick method should be called roughly 60 times per second, therefore each frame will be displayed for about threshold ÷ 60 seconds

        Parameters:
        t - New value for threshold

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops the animation, and resets the displayed frame to the starting frame. Does nothing if already stopped

      • tick

        public void tick()
        Should be called 60 times per second, within a tick thread
